beer.beer_description: Dos Equis is a lager that was originally brewed by the German-born Mexican brewer Wilhelm Hasse  in 1897. The brand was named "Siglo XX" ("20th century") to commemorate the arrival of the new century, and the bottles were marked with the Roman numerals "XX", or "Dos Equis" (two X).
